WEBVTT

00:01.058 --> 00:02.700
Hey there, and welcome to Soul Church.

00:03.300 --> 00:07.124
Our prayer is that this message encourages you wherever you may be in life.

00:07.705 --> 00:12.710
We've been hearing so many stories about what God is doing in people's lives, and we'd love to hear yours.

00:13.050 --> 00:17.575
So take a second and send your story to stories at soulchurch.com.

00:17.595 --> 00:21.639
Thanks again for joining us today, and we hope that you enjoy the message.

00:22.040 --> 00:22.560
God bless.

00:25.023 --> 00:28.146
Lord, as we receive your word today,

00:28.930 --> 00:37.060
As we hear vision for the year, fresh vision, pray, Father God, that we wouldn't just hear it, we'd run with it.

00:37.080 --> 00:41.846
Or this wouldn't just be a word, it wouldn't just be information, but it would be something that we take hold of today.

00:42.807 --> 00:44.589
It would light a fresh fire in our hearts.

00:45.691 --> 00:51.918
I know many people have been serving Jesus in this room for decades and decades, but today would be a new day.

00:52.919 --> 00:58.226
For those who are new to faith, Father God, that faith would continue to ignite and grow.

00:58.754 --> 01:02.979
and strengthen in Jesus name.

01:02.999 --> 01:03.420
Amen.

01:03.860 --> 01:04.281
Amen.

01:04.481 --> 01:05.483
Come on, let's thank God.

01:09.568 --> 01:10.549
You may be seated.

01:10.569 --> 01:12.832
A huge welcome to our online community.

01:14.053 --> 01:15.115
So great that you're with us.

01:18.519 --> 01:19.300
It's busy Sunday.

01:20.321 --> 01:21.963
We've had to open the field next door.

01:22.945 --> 01:24.386
It's incredible what God is doing.

01:25.608 --> 01:27.250
All right, you're ready for the Word of God.

01:28.546 --> 01:30.068
Chantal and I love this church.

01:30.168 --> 01:31.070
We need you to know that.

01:31.671 --> 01:33.974
We love you dearly and we love pastoring you.

01:34.795 --> 01:36.638
We love preaching and teaching God's Word.

01:36.678 --> 01:38.320
We love our staff, our dream team.

01:39.222 --> 01:43.188
But our deepest passion is lost people finding Christ.

01:45.111 --> 01:58.290
When people come to the front, when people lift up their hands, when Jimmy or one of the team on a Friday night or in kids, the teams respond to the gospel, it lights a fire that nothing else can.

01:59.042 --> 01:59.663
in our lives.

02:01.024 --> 02:05.949
And the UK has not been as hungry for the gospel in our lifetimes.

02:07.071 --> 02:11.615
There is an awakening happening, a great awakening happening to Christianity right now.

02:13.658 --> 02:22.527
I've lived through, in my lifetime I've lived through the sexual revolution, the cultural revolution, the digital revolution, and now we are experiencing a Jesus revolution.

02:24.669 --> 02:28.914
Generations have prayed for this moment.

02:30.370 --> 02:41.364
On Thursday night, at Seoul Central, I walked in and there was 104 people off the back of the wonder and there was 104 people on Alpha Course, again, which is the record.

02:41.384 --> 02:42.606
We've never seen anything like that.

02:44.348 --> 02:46.350
75 people in the Bible study.

02:47.672 --> 02:50.456
People couldn't get in the room to study the Bible.

02:52.218 --> 02:53.680
When I grew up, that wasn't happening.

02:54.160 --> 02:56.283
You'd find every excuse possible not to.

02:56.323 --> 02:58.546
Now people are desperate.

02:59.618 --> 03:00.660
to hear the word of God.

03:01.341 --> 03:05.467
And the leading demographic in the UK church right now is Gen Z males.

03:07.370 --> 03:12.257
They said that Gen Z would be the first atheistic generation and they got it wrong.

03:13.579 --> 03:15.983
This is the revival generation.

03:17.505 --> 03:20.189
I'll tell you what, you are the revival generation.

03:20.209 --> 03:24.075
To every student, young and old, you are the revival generation.

03:24.676 --> 03:26.098
There is a stirring happening.

03:28.258 --> 03:33.165
People are hungrier than ever for the Bible, for the Word of God.

03:34.226 --> 03:43.399
So every year, Chantal and I, we seek God, we pray, and we ask God, what is the specific direction for our church for the new year?

03:44.360 --> 03:47.744
Last year was choose joy, and it was fantastic, even though it was challenging.

03:48.185 --> 03:51.790
And it's not that we're not gonna choose joy for 2026, keep choosing joy.

03:52.691 --> 03:56.096
And it's not we did advance the couple of years before, you gotta keep advancing in life.

03:56.156 --> 03:57.778
So none of these words stop.

03:59.426 --> 04:02.949
I think there needs to be a fresh sense of God, what are you saying this year?

04:05.332 --> 04:10.597
And so our key passage for 2026 comes from Matthew 28, verse 16.

04:12.058 --> 04:13.459
It's known as the Great Commission.

04:14.701 --> 04:26.132
It cured just after Christ's resurrection, it occurred on a mountain in Galilee, and this was Christ's final instructions before his ascension to his disciples and to the people.

04:26.972 --> 04:28.594
It says, then the 11 disciples

04:28.930 --> 04:34.457
went to Galilee to the mountain where Jesus had told them to go and when they saw him, they worshiped him, but some doubted.

04:34.497 --> 04:40.044
Then Jesus came to them and said, all authority in heaven on earth has been given to me.

04:41.066 --> 04:42.307
Come on, let's now read this together.

04:43.108 --> 04:56.626
Therefore go and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father, the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, and teaching them to obey everything I have commanded you.

04:57.058 --> 05:01.865
and surely I am with you always to the very end of the age.

05:02.907 --> 05:15.726
When we read this passage, we felt a stirring clearly to gather the church back to the great commission, that his commission would become our mission.

05:16.807 --> 05:22.355
This was Christ's last command that we need to make our first priority.

05:24.719 --> 05:26.802
Our theme for 20 years

05:26.882 --> 05:30.906
26 is we're on mission.

05:32.428 --> 05:34.470
As a church, we're on mission.

05:35.051 --> 05:54.152
We're not on our own mission, we're on his mission, which is the great commission, to go into all the world and make disciples of all nations, baptize Him in the name of the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit, and do not fear for He is with us always, even to the end of the age.

05:54.652 --> 05:56.434
This is our mission.

05:56.706 --> 05:59.589
2026, will you choose to accept?

06:05.554 --> 06:14.162
I believe that 2026, not just for soul church, but for the church in the United Kingdom, will be an awakening of the Great Commission.

06:15.464 --> 06:20.729
And so we're going to align and refocus that we are a mission focused church.

06:20.749 --> 06:26.514
2026 will be the return of the Great Commission.

06:27.010 --> 06:28.272
his mission to the church.

06:29.834 --> 06:40.310
A church on mission doesn't believe that we just exist for ourselves, but we exist for our city, our county, our nation, and our world.

06:41.872 --> 06:44.916
We are a great commission church.

06:45.658 --> 06:54.130
Now the challenge for the church is our tendency is we gather, but God's called us to go.

06:56.322 --> 06:58.104
There's a difference between gathering and going.

06:58.664 --> 07:00.426
This is a gathering of believers.

07:01.707 --> 07:03.850
And I think it's fantastic.

07:03.870 --> 07:06.472
And Jesus gathered, constantly gathered His disciples.

07:06.512 --> 07:07.573
They met in the upper room.

07:07.754 --> 07:08.594
They went to the courts.

07:08.634 --> 07:09.495
They went to the temple.

07:09.515 --> 07:10.817
They went to all those places.

07:11.177 --> 07:14.681
But Jesus said, it's not just about gathering, it's about going.

07:16.462 --> 07:20.847
And so as a church, we've been really good at gathering and we're going to stay good at gathering.

07:20.867 --> 07:24.050
But this next 12 months, we're going to focus on going.

07:26.274 --> 07:28.738
You see, gathering is actually a lot easier than going.

07:30.060 --> 07:32.904
But God has called us to go.

07:32.944 --> 07:35.688
Now, I love this nation.

07:36.249 --> 07:38.313
A lot of people have written the nation off, but I haven't.

07:39.114 --> 07:41.718
I'm a patriot of the United Kingdom.

07:41.738 --> 07:52.534
But I am absolutely convinced the best thing for our country right now is a Christ-centered, healthy, vibrant, life-giving, mission-focused church.

07:54.197 --> 07:54.898
The best thing.

07:56.546 --> 08:02.533
The health of the United Kingdom is directly connected to the church on mission.

08:04.995 --> 08:08.900
We can criticize and we can get frustrated and we can get angry about so many issues.

08:09.540 --> 08:18.250
The reality is the only hope left for the nation of England, the United Kingdom, is a church united through Jesus Christ.

08:19.751 --> 08:25.778
The church should be casting a shadow on the nation, not the nation casting a shadow

08:25.858 --> 08:26.539
on the church.

08:29.202 --> 08:36.270
We're going to do that this year as we buy wheelchairs for children in the community foundation.

08:36.290 --> 08:39.654
What we do in the church is casting a shadow saying, we see you.

08:40.795 --> 08:46.522
We see you as we help a family in crisis in our community who've lost a loved one.

08:46.962 --> 08:48.144
We send money to support.

08:48.164 --> 08:48.824
What are we doing?

08:48.864 --> 08:49.866
We're saying, we see you.

08:50.787 --> 08:51.407
We see you.

08:52.068 --> 08:53.089
We're not just gathering.

08:53.129 --> 08:53.810
We're going.

08:55.202 --> 08:57.606
We're not just here to gather where God's call us to go.

08:59.108 --> 09:02.934
I believe the shadow of the church should be creating justice, mercy and compassion.

09:05.278 --> 09:13.150
People who live to undermine the church need to be careful because if you take away from this, if you take away the church from this nation, it will fall quickly.

09:14.051 --> 09:16.134
It will fall.

09:16.154 --> 09:16.395
Why?

09:16.876 --> 09:19.860
Because the church is the bedrock of society.

09:20.822 --> 09:23.666
It is the foundation of community.

09:24.482 --> 09:32.751
Conservative estimation says the local church in the United Kingdom adds 55 billion pounds in social and economic value.

09:34.312 --> 09:34.813
That's huge.

09:35.974 --> 09:38.276
That's what we bring to our cities.

09:39.758 --> 09:45.904
And I believe that God has called us to be stewards of the church for this generation.

09:47.406 --> 09:49.548
So here's our word for the year.

09:49.568 --> 09:50.148
We're on mission.

09:51.049 --> 09:51.730
We're on mission.

09:53.250 --> 09:57.437
and our nation needs us on mission, but every mission needs a mandate.

09:58.639 --> 10:06.832
And I want to share real quick three mandates for us to run with to see whether you choose to accept it.

10:07.493 --> 10:11.239
Number one is our mission begins with vision.

10:12.601 --> 10:13.763
Mission begins with vision.

10:15.766 --> 10:20.594
At the very start of Jesus ministry, before he said, go into all the world,

10:21.218 --> 10:27.446
The very start, one of his opening lines in John chapter 4, verse 35, he said to his disciples, he says, open your eyes.

10:28.928 --> 10:30.310
Open your eyes, soul church.

10:30.851 --> 10:31.712
And look at the city.

10:32.433 --> 10:33.855
It is ripe for harvest.

10:34.596 --> 10:36.378
Norwich and Norfolk is ready.

10:37.560 --> 10:38.221
We are ready.

10:38.361 --> 10:39.302
Chroma is ready.

10:41.005 --> 10:41.886
Chroma is ready.

10:42.807 --> 10:43.668
Deiram is ready.

10:43.748 --> 10:44.830
Great Yarmith is ready.

10:45.090 --> 10:46.812
It is ready for a harvest.

10:47.293 --> 10:51.058
But we've got to open our eyes to see what God wants to do.

10:51.586 --> 10:53.409
We cannot reach what we cannot see.

10:55.051 --> 10:57.274
And mission always begins with vision.

10:58.276 --> 11:01.340
Before God ever sends us on anything, he shows us.

11:02.782 --> 11:06.107
And so if we stop seeing it, we'll stop going.

11:07.308 --> 11:09.812
Do we still see the poverty around us?

11:09.832 --> 11:11.394
Do we see the brokenness, the hurt?

11:12.055 --> 11:17.623
Do we see the lost or do we choose just to gather and stay comfortable and stationary?

11:18.625 --> 11:19.666
The question is,

11:20.578 --> 11:21.559
our eyes open.

11:22.581 --> 11:33.357
This series and this whole year is going to be built around this theme on mission, but one of the things it will do is it will cause us to open our eyes, to open our eyes.

11:36.162 --> 11:40.368
Because if we don't see the city, the families, the brokenness, the lost, who will see them?

11:41.530 --> 11:42.291
Who will see them?

11:43.052 --> 11:49.522
Matthew 936 says, Jesus saw the crowds and he was moved with compassion.

11:51.618 --> 11:56.966
See, the older we get in our faith, we forget what life was like before Jesus.

11:57.968 --> 12:00.932
Some of you have been serving Jesus a long time, and I commend you.

12:01.593 --> 12:04.979
Some of it's 50, 60, even up to 70 years, you've been serving Jesus.

12:05.459 --> 12:06.501
You've been coming to church.

12:06.521 --> 12:08.524
You've heard more sermons you can remember.

12:11.589 --> 12:13.992
You know what happens when you serve Jesus a long, long time?

12:14.714 --> 12:15.635
You stop seeing.

12:17.277 --> 12:20.242
You continue to gather, but you stop going.

12:22.210 --> 12:26.496
And then people who come and they find Christ for the first time and their eyes are open.

12:27.477 --> 12:29.300
Next week, they've got three new people with them.

12:30.722 --> 12:31.302
You ever seen that?

12:33.846 --> 12:40.555
They've got three, you know, like, oh, I haven't brought anyone to church in 10 years because you've stopped seeing.

12:42.157 --> 12:43.779
You're gathering, but you're not going.

12:45.702 --> 12:48.626
God wants us this year to be aware

12:50.722 --> 12:52.205
of the need around us.

12:53.567 --> 12:55.590
You see, when we stop seeing, we stop going.

12:57.393 --> 13:03.043
I encourage you, don't stop your children from seeing things, from seeing poverty and seeing pain.

13:04.265 --> 13:07.370
You know, we can shoulder our kids so much, they don't see it.

13:08.492 --> 13:10.876
You see, we're never responsible for what we don't see.

13:12.599 --> 13:13.120
Say that again.

13:13.741 --> 13:16.786
We're never responsible for what we don't see.

13:18.402 --> 13:20.545
Take your children and speak to a homeless person.

13:20.585 --> 13:22.407
Let your children hear their story.

13:23.989 --> 13:24.589
Let them listen.

13:24.629 --> 13:26.251
Let them take them a cake, a sausage drop.

13:26.632 --> 13:27.873
Listen to them.

13:28.033 --> 13:33.079
It's not enough for us just to see poverty for a screen or a brochure.

13:33.099 --> 13:34.321
We've got to see poverty.

13:34.341 --> 13:38.005
We've got to look into the eyes of someone who's lost and broken and hurting.

13:38.025 --> 13:41.970
And we've got to see and feel what they're seeing and what they're feeling.

13:46.274 --> 13:48.297
We never feel responsible for what we cannot see.

13:48.317 --> 13:55.027
When I was 17, I can't even believe my mom and dad let me do this, but went to Nigeria for three months, 17.

13:56.610 --> 13:58.793
Put me on a plane and no phones, by the way.

13:58.813 --> 14:00.335
We had one phone call in three months.

14:01.077 --> 14:02.899
We had to travel two hours to a phone box.

14:03.520 --> 14:04.402
Three minutes we got.

14:05.964 --> 14:07.707
We spent half the call going, can you hear me?

14:07.747 --> 14:08.107
You there?

14:08.287 --> 14:08.628
Hello?

14:08.668 --> 14:11.492
I'm like, Mom, we've got to have to get on with this quick.

14:11.512 --> 14:12.073
We're alive.

14:14.537 --> 14:15.218
You know when we went,

14:15.746 --> 14:22.414
When Graham Hollinger and I, we went to Nigeria and we saw children in the school dying of malaria, passing away.

14:24.095 --> 14:24.636
I saw it.

14:26.398 --> 14:31.544
Something got inside of me when we moved to South Africa and I love Africa.

14:32.565 --> 14:33.666
I love the nation of Africa.

14:33.847 --> 14:38.892
Chantal and I are traveling to Uganda soon because we want to see the work that is continuing through our church in Uganda.

14:39.153 --> 14:40.434
And I want my kids to see it.

14:41.474 --> 14:43.176
Don't shelter your kids from pain.

14:43.416 --> 14:44.818
I'm not talking about putting them in danger.

14:44.958 --> 14:50.305
I'm talking about letting them see it because if they don't see it, they'll never have an opportunity to change it.

14:55.071 --> 14:57.954
You know, we don't even have to go as far as Africa to see poverty.

14:58.795 --> 15:00.057
There's lost people all around us.

15:01.058 --> 15:10.770
The person at work at the desk that's going through a divorce, the friend at school who's been constantly bullied, the homeless person on our streets,

15:11.586 --> 15:14.971
You see, if we choose not to see it, we don't have to do anything about it.

15:16.734 --> 15:18.577
I believe this church has actually been marked.

15:19.979 --> 15:22.303
John Drake gave me a word when we first saw a soldier.

15:22.363 --> 15:24.666
He said, John God has marked this church for the city.

15:25.668 --> 15:26.209
He was right.

15:26.549 --> 15:27.210
We've been marked.

15:28.072 --> 15:31.998
And we can either just keep gathering or we can gather and go.

15:32.038 --> 15:34.382
It's our choice.

15:34.842 --> 15:36.625
Too many churches just gavel without going.

15:37.627 --> 15:39.730
When you gavel without going, you end up squabbling.

15:41.410 --> 15:44.073
You end up fighting, because you see all the problems within.

15:44.955 --> 15:48.699
But when you go, suddenly the problem outside your walls is bigger than one inside your walls.

15:50.101 --> 15:51.483
God has called us to go.

15:54.767 --> 15:57.030
And this is our first mandate, give me eyes to see.

15:58.152 --> 15:59.273
Our mission begins with vision.

15:59.333 --> 16:07.023
Number two is that our mission is focused on what is lost.

16:07.584 --> 16:09.266
Give me a wave of your easily distracted.

16:10.146 --> 16:11.588
Where's all the easily distracted people?

16:12.809 --> 16:17.274
Now give me a wave if you are not easily distracted, but you're distracted by everyone who's easily distracted.

16:19.316 --> 16:20.397
But why do they keep walking it out?

16:20.417 --> 16:22.239
Why do they keep, just focus.

16:22.760 --> 16:24.221
So we're all distracted, yes.

16:24.241 --> 16:27.244
So we're either distracted or distracted by the people who distract us.

16:30.088 --> 16:31.189
Now I'm easily distracted.

16:32.130 --> 16:33.191
If you didn't know, now you do.

16:35.093 --> 16:36.114
Do you know Jesus?

16:36.642 --> 16:40.187
One of his qualities, one of Jesus' qualities was he was easily distracted.

16:41.448 --> 16:42.690
Do you know what distracted people?

16:43.391 --> 16:46.515
What distracted Jesus was lost people.

16:46.535 --> 16:50.100
Throughout the Bible he raised from the dead and he got distracted.

16:51.461 --> 16:54.646
He was everywhere he went, he got distracted because he just loved people.

16:56.428 --> 16:57.529
Luke 19, 10.

16:58.591 --> 17:02.155
This was the only time in Scripture that we actually read.

17:02.215 --> 17:04.178
What was the mission of Christ?

17:04.354 --> 17:06.818
The only one thing he ever told, what was his mission on earth?

17:06.838 --> 17:07.559
This is what he said.

17:07.579 --> 17:15.973
He said, for the son of man came to seek, hang on, wait for this, to see, number one, man in number one, and to save, to go.

17:17.676 --> 17:24.167
His mission is our mission, to seek and to save that which is lost.

17:26.811 --> 17:30.898
Now write this down, we're always distracted by what's lost.

17:32.514 --> 17:35.718
Who's ever lost their phone or their remote control down the side of the couch?

17:38.301 --> 17:44.588
Who knows in the moment when the phone and the remote is down the side of the couch, you're not thinking, I'm so glad I've found a couch.

17:47.692 --> 17:48.873
You ain't worried about the couch.

17:49.414 --> 17:50.415
You're worried about the remote.

17:50.976 --> 17:54.480
All you can think about is the distraction of the remote.

17:55.341 --> 17:59.506
You'll walk past all the found things in your life to find the lost thing.

18:00.002 --> 18:06.812
If you lose your keys, you will search your house up and down to fight, try and find what is lost, and you do not care about what's been found."

18:08.474 --> 18:09.656
This is what Jesus was saying.

18:12.080 --> 18:17.407
So many times in church, we get obsessed with what's already been found.

18:18.469 --> 18:19.891
Well, they didn't see my favorite song today.

18:20.492 --> 18:23.617
Songs are too new, songs are too old, songs are too loud, songs are too soft.

18:23.677 --> 18:24.658
I get the emails.

18:28.514 --> 18:31.177
And what we do is we get obsessed with the found things.

18:32.058 --> 18:34.501
And does it mean that Jesus doesn't love us and care about us?

18:34.541 --> 18:35.502
Of course he does.

18:36.723 --> 18:39.847
He's obsessed with what's been lost.

18:40.888 --> 18:51.200
Just like you and I, when we lose something and we become obsessed in that moment by what is lost, Jesus is obsessed with your friend at work who's lost.

18:55.865 --> 18:56.466
Obsessed.

18:57.122 --> 19:01.448
He said, I've come to seek and to save the found.

19:03.311 --> 19:04.833
No, he said, the lost.

19:05.955 --> 19:06.876
Here's some breaking news.

19:07.256 --> 19:11.102
Heaven is my eternal home and every problem on earth will be fixed.

19:12.203 --> 19:15.188
Every single problem you're worried about right now is done in heaven.

19:16.089 --> 19:16.470
Finished.

19:17.110 --> 19:18.272
You are going to live healthy.

19:18.492 --> 19:19.394
You're going to live forever.

19:19.654 --> 19:20.796
You're going to live strong.

19:21.156 --> 19:25.202
I'm not going to go into any more details because my theology will go wrong, but it's going to be good.

19:27.554 --> 19:28.716
You ain't got to worry about heaven.

19:31.800 --> 19:34.583
And it's not that Jesus doesn't care about the 99.

19:34.843 --> 19:39.209
It's just that he's obsessed and distracted by the one.

19:39.229 --> 19:41.152
A wonder of the one still distracts you.

19:42.634 --> 19:45.738
A wonder of the one still moves us.

19:47.059 --> 19:50.864
A wonder of the one person in the cafe after the service who's sitting there alone.

19:50.884 --> 19:55.250
A wonder if you still see them or are you obsessed with the found people in your group?

19:59.618 --> 20:05.044
I wonder if the person sitting alone in church still distracts you, but you've got to get to the cool clan.

20:06.846 --> 20:07.686
Do you see what I'm saying?

20:07.706 --> 20:13.192
Are we obsessed with the found or obsessed with the lost?

20:13.252 --> 20:16.135
Because Jesus came to seek and to save the lost.

20:16.896 --> 20:17.857
My ticket's in my hand.

20:17.877 --> 20:18.538
I know where I'm going.

20:19.899 --> 20:22.021
If I never heard another sermon, I'm good.

20:23.163 --> 20:24.284
