20:24.384 --> 20:24.664
I'm good.

20:25.605 --> 20:26.386
I know where I'm going.

20:26.626 --> 20:33.913
I have one mission on this earth, which is the great commission, to take as many people with me to my heavily destination as I can.

20:45.324 --> 20:46.705
I'm going to brag on one of our elders.

20:47.286 --> 20:48.827
She's our good friend, Sharon Hollinger.

20:49.608 --> 20:51.210
She is incredible at finding the one.

20:52.431 --> 20:54.313
We had them over the other night.

20:54.333 --> 20:55.634
We were talking about these things.

20:56.418 --> 20:58.481
You know, every Sunday she brings someone to church.

20:59.723 --> 21:06.473
Someone in her workplace or her work world that's maybe going for a challenge or interested or just asking questions about life.

21:06.974 --> 21:12.042
She talked 10 people that she's found, have found Christ from her world since we started church.

21:12.783 --> 21:14.205
I'm thinking this is just amazing.

21:16.068 --> 21:19.193
And she'll tell you herself, the religious stuff in church just is like war off a duck.

21:19.213 --> 21:22.738
But she is obsessed with people who were lost.

21:23.810 --> 21:26.516
I wonder whether you're obsessed with what's found or what's been lost.

21:27.799 --> 21:29.362
I've been so challenged by this thought.

21:30.164 --> 21:35.475
I couldn't sleep on Friday night when I got this revelation that Jesus is obsessed by what's lost.

21:36.016 --> 21:40.466
But I spend so much of my worry and my care on what's been found.

21:42.978 --> 21:45.762
Now, Jesus wants us to grow in Him and be discipled.

21:46.142 --> 21:52.851
He wants us to go to conferences and events so we have our faith renewed and we get a fresh fire and our belly and all those things.

21:53.032 --> 21:54.654
He's not against any of those things.

21:55.054 --> 22:00.041
He just wants you to know that you're on mission to seek and to save the lost.

22:00.061 --> 22:06.570
So as our church this year, our mission is to focus on what is lost, our prayer mission, our mission, our giving, our teaching.

22:06.950 --> 22:09.554
We're going to go after the lost at all costs.

22:12.834 --> 22:15.919
Now, you might not believe what I'm about to say, but I do, because it's in the Scriptures.

22:16.760 --> 22:18.903
Everything is signaling right now.

22:22.088 --> 22:24.953
Across the earth to the return of Jesus Christ.

22:25.854 --> 22:26.235
Everything.

22:27.717 --> 22:30.561
Kind of weirds us out when we talk about it, because we're like, oh, what does that mean?

22:30.642 --> 22:32.965
And we'd prefer not even to talk about it.

22:33.005 --> 22:37.272
But I'm not an eschatologist, a big eschatologist.

22:37.332 --> 22:39.175
I don't have the knowledge and all that.

22:39.195 --> 22:41.298
I leave it to the others, but I full on believing it.

22:41.954 --> 22:43.416
Jesus is coming back again.

22:45.038 --> 22:46.020
He's coming back again.

22:49.385 --> 22:51.868
People just need to hear the good news.

22:53.891 --> 22:56.314
People ask me a lot, where do I get my drive from?

22:57.015 --> 22:58.517
And I thought about that a lot over Christmas.

22:58.698 --> 23:01.722
You know, my biggest drive comes from lost people.

23:03.084 --> 23:07.410
It's the fact that we have an opportunity in this city to share the good news.

23:08.322 --> 23:12.929
And I'm actually, when I reflected on this, I'm actually not at my happiest preaching here.

23:12.949 --> 23:14.071
I love preaching to the sheep.

23:14.171 --> 23:15.332
I love preaching to you guys.

23:15.913 --> 23:23.004
I'm at my happiest when I'm in a room of unchurched people who are lost, and I get to share my story.

23:24.286 --> 23:27.210
That's where I'm at my absolute fulfillment fulfilled.

23:27.290 --> 23:29.754
I've led people to church in a gym.

23:29.774 --> 23:31.516
I was one of my close friend Spencer.

23:31.596 --> 23:33.139
I led him to the Lord in a sauna.

23:35.162 --> 23:35.903
We're in a sauna.

23:35.923 --> 23:36.884
I was like, how are you guys?

23:37.045 --> 23:38.066
My life's a mess.

23:38.274 --> 23:40.698
And then I shared the gospel, he started crying, it was a big mess.

23:41.579 --> 23:44.164
And we led into the Lord and the Son, his family is now in church.

23:45.566 --> 23:47.369
We're not just talking about bringing people to church.

23:48.891 --> 23:55.282
We're talking about actually how do we help you go on mission this year in leading someone to Christ.

23:56.386 --> 23:57.828
You know, some people don't even know how to do it.

23:57.909 --> 23:59.371
I feel responsible as a pastor.

23:59.391 --> 24:01.455
We're actually going to help the church this year.

24:01.835 --> 24:12.313
We're going to empower you and educate and train you and disciple you to lead somebody to Jesus where you grab their hand in a restaurant and you say, can I lead you to Jesus?

24:14.517 --> 24:15.419
Time is close.

24:16.701 --> 24:18.284
Jesus modeled this on the cross.

24:18.344 --> 24:19.406
The fees are on the cross.

24:19.426 --> 24:20.928
He turned to one, he ignored him.

24:20.948 --> 24:21.970
He turned to the other.

24:23.010 --> 24:24.371
He knew his time was close.

24:24.411 --> 24:25.493
He was moments away.

24:25.533 --> 24:28.215
Yeah, he gave him his mission statement.

24:28.816 --> 24:31.459
He says, today you will be with me in paradise.

24:32.320 --> 24:41.869
His heart is that none would perish, but all should have eternal life.

24:41.889 --> 24:47.055
In Luke chapter three, Jesus tells three parables back to back of a lost sheep, a lost coin, a lost son.

24:47.915 --> 24:50.418
The moral of the all three stories is the same.

24:51.042 --> 24:55.448
Jesus is willing to leave all of the found ones to save the lost one.

24:56.269 --> 24:58.592
Do you know the story of the lost sheep makes no sense?

24:59.574 --> 25:04.040
You've got 99 sheep who are saved, flipped half or cared for, and you lose one.

25:04.721 --> 25:07.264
Well, if I'm in business, 99% return is good.

25:08.086 --> 25:08.807
Yeah, are we all good?

25:09.808 --> 25:11.070
But Jesus says, no, no, no.

25:11.570 --> 25:12.732
I care so much.

25:13.513 --> 25:19.922
You guys just stick together, help each other, protect each other, and I'm going after the one who's lost.

25:20.610 --> 25:21.791
I'm not willing.

25:22.031 --> 25:24.794
Jesus is not willing for one to perish.

25:26.376 --> 25:34.924
I was speaking to a lady before after the service, and she was talking about her son and the problem she has with her son, and she said it's almost impossible for him to come to Christ.

25:34.944 --> 25:38.368
I said, no, no, he can't be too far gone.

25:39.049 --> 25:41.251
We don't know how far gone that sheep was.

25:41.271 --> 25:48.498
He could have been in 10 fields over, but Jesus was prepared to jump over the fence, run through the fields, to grab the one sheep.

25:48.578 --> 25:52.162
But it was gone and say, I'm here to seek that which is lost.

25:54.585 --> 25:56.327
Now, I've only lost, I want to finish this story.

25:56.348 --> 25:58.050
I've only ever lost a child once.

26:00.573 --> 26:03.456
I told this story before, but I'm going to put a different angle on it.

26:06.160 --> 26:18.034
When Justice, I think he was either six or seven, he was... And we were in Sainsbury's, my daughter was with us, and I turned out

26:18.626 --> 26:21.449
Where two kids, one was a stayer, one was a runner.

26:22.250 --> 26:23.391
It's normally the trend in families.

26:23.791 --> 26:26.474
If you've got more than two kids and you've got two or three runners, you're in trouble.

26:26.494 --> 26:27.174
I'm just putting it there.

26:27.715 --> 26:28.696
Miracle was a stayer.

26:28.756 --> 26:29.757
She just stayed beside me.

26:30.177 --> 26:31.359
She just loves to be close.

26:31.379 --> 26:33.060
But justice is a different story.

26:33.381 --> 26:34.061
That kid runs.

26:35.322 --> 26:36.163
He runs for his life.

26:36.223 --> 26:37.365
And I turned around.

26:37.405 --> 26:38.005
We're in the cereals.

26:38.045 --> 26:39.407
I turned around and he's gone.

26:40.688 --> 26:44.351
And your heart, as a parent, just oof.

26:44.371 --> 26:46.994
And so I'm running around, saying, he's trying to find him.

26:47.522 --> 26:51.368
So I head to where I thought, if I go to the exit, if I hit the exit, at least I know.

26:52.169 --> 26:56.195
And as I'm getting to the exit, there's a lady walking in with my son.

26:58.138 --> 26:59.560
And she's like, is this anyone's son?

26:59.600 --> 27:00.361
I'm like, no, it's not mine.

27:00.381 --> 27:00.802
I was not mine.

27:02.725 --> 27:03.847
I said, yes, he's mine.

27:04.327 --> 27:06.130
He's mine to justice that comes running in.

27:06.531 --> 27:07.732
He doesn't care one little bit.

27:09.856 --> 27:11.498
Now, imagine this story.

27:12.219 --> 27:12.900
Imagine this scenario.

27:12.920 --> 27:15.604
It didn't happen, but I want you to imagine it did happen.

27:15.624 --> 27:16.786
Imagine as I am

27:18.338 --> 27:22.763
running around Sainsbury's desperately trying to find my lost son.

27:23.204 --> 27:25.126
My daughter is tugging on my jacket.

27:25.226 --> 27:28.210
Daddy, daddy, can I have a snack?

27:28.230 --> 27:29.771
Daddy, daddy, can I go to the toilet?

27:31.654 --> 27:36.559
Who knows that that is not important when I'm looking for my lost son.

27:38.021 --> 27:39.703
Do you know that can be the picture of the church?

27:42.046 --> 27:45.650
We can be pulling on the curtails and trying to

27:45.858 --> 27:51.311
get upset about what's not happening in church and what is, and they offended me.

27:51.451 --> 27:58.046
And God is saying, yeah, but what is the mission?

28:00.733 --> 28:01.795
You don't need a snack.

28:02.437 --> 28:04.722
You need to go and find the person who's lost.

28:05.474 --> 28:10.721
Sometimes we get so caught up in church snacks and church politics and the little things.

28:10.741 --> 28:14.887
And she said this and he said that, that we start becoming internal instead of external.

28:15.087 --> 28:16.990
We start looking inwards instead of outwards.

28:17.270 --> 28:20.615
And I want to encourage you this year, we are a church on mission.

28:20.835 --> 28:23.218
We are looking in Sainsbury's for the last child.

28:23.438 --> 28:25.661
We're looking for the last one, the one without hope.

28:31.850 --> 28:34.994
The heart of the father is yes, he sees you, he loves you.

28:36.002 --> 28:37.203
He's seeking after them.

28:38.485 --> 28:46.915
As a church on mission this year, let's not get caught up in anything that can distract us from the mission.

28:47.757 --> 28:53.964
If you've got a fence against Chantal or I, anyone in this church, I will encourage you.

28:54.505 --> 29:05.138
It's just a snack compared to the Great Commission, which is to go after, to seek and to save that

29:05.250 --> 29:06.031
which is lost.

29:07.654 --> 29:08.555
Don't be distracted.

29:09.837 --> 29:12.621
Don't be because things will come and they'll come and they come to us too.

29:14.304 --> 29:14.844
Put it right.

29:16.587 --> 29:23.057
People say to me all the time, when you're going to teach on the end times, when you unveil the seven scrolls and unpack the seven seals.

29:25.721 --> 29:26.862
We're going to do that in Bible study.

29:28.164 --> 29:28.825
We're going to do that.

29:30.468 --> 29:34.674
But when people come into this atmosphere, we're going to give them hope.

29:36.034 --> 29:36.755
We're gonna give them help.

29:38.257 --> 29:38.878
We're gonna love them.

29:40.299 --> 29:41.921
It's not that those things aren't important.

29:41.982 --> 29:43.764
It's just, I can't change any of those things.

29:44.705 --> 29:48.510
The only thing we can do is point people to Jesus.

29:49.631 --> 29:54.117
The greatest use of a human life is to point people to Jesus.

29:58.062 --> 30:00.285
To all of our students, God has brought you here.

30:01.807 --> 30:04.370
God has brought you here to the NUA, to the UEA.

30:04.866 --> 30:07.609
We're so grateful that you said yes to Norwich, it's the finest city.

30:11.194 --> 30:11.915
But you're on mission.

30:13.436 --> 30:14.297
You're on mission this year.

30:15.078 --> 30:20.565
Your number one assignment isn't your assignment, it's this assignment.

30:20.585 --> 30:23.709
No one can reach the UEA apart from you lot.

30:24.890 --> 30:29.356
And we commission you to go on his great commission.

30:29.376 --> 30:34.482
God has brought you here to seek and to save those students who are lost.

30:36.034 --> 30:37.516
Lost people matter to God.

30:38.878 --> 30:40.781
The question is, do lost people matter to me?

30:43.345 --> 30:44.487
So we're out with focused.

30:45.648 --> 30:48.813
And if it annoys you that this year, we're gonna be extra out with focused, I'm sorry.

30:49.935 --> 30:51.257
But as I say, time is short.

30:52.759 --> 30:56.124
And so that's the mission for 2026.

30:56.965 --> 30:57.987
That's the great commission.

30:58.989 --> 30:59.830
Will you accept it?

31:00.371 --> 31:01.252
Will you come on board?

31:04.236 --> 31:05.298
That's the mission mandate.

31:06.338 --> 31:07.399
We're on Mission Church.

31:08.741 --> 31:12.126
We've got a city, a county, a nation to reach with the love of Jesus.

31:13.367 --> 31:14.048
It's our time.

31:15.110 --> 31:16.752
We're gonna preach the gospel more this year.

31:16.792 --> 31:19.676
I felt compelled to preach the gospel.

31:20.838 --> 31:23.641
You say, well, I hear, I hear, I know what the gospel is.

31:24.062 --> 31:25.364
You've got many, many people done.

31:26.485 --> 31:36.018
I figured if we keep preaching the gospel, maybe you'll understand how to do it and maybe you'll be able to do it as well in your workplace to talk to people from the start to the end and lead them.

31:36.290 --> 31:36.931
to Jesus.

31:37.852 --> 31:39.954
Now, we've got a gift for you.

31:39.974 --> 31:40.634
Those in the room.

31:42.837 --> 31:45.900
I'm gonna ask the host team just to hand them out now.

31:46.640 --> 31:49.403
It'll get a little bit, sound a bit like Christmas in here for the next few moments.

31:51.105 --> 31:55.950
It's a little sticker that says on mission and a wristband that says on mission with Matthew 28, 19.

31:57.571 --> 32:04.338
We do this because it's a reminder that when you wake up tomorrow on Monday morning, you're on mission.

32:04.770 --> 32:08.313
You say, well, I don't really like Mondays, or you got a mission.

32:08.333 --> 32:08.994
Mission Monday.

32:10.035 --> 32:11.216
To share the love of Jesus.

32:12.077 --> 32:14.199
To look out for the loss, the broken, the hurting.

32:15.420 --> 32:16.942
There's a little sticker in there as well.

32:16.982 --> 32:19.985
You can put it on your phone, your laptop, the cat, anywhere.

32:20.265 --> 32:21.506
You're going to see it regularly.

32:23.168 --> 32:23.929
I'm joking.

32:23.949 --> 32:24.950
Don't send emails.

32:31.156 --> 32:32.757
Some of you don't like wearing wristbands.

32:32.877 --> 32:33.458
