32:33.794 --> 32:38.227
Would you just put it on just for this moment, because we're going to pray in a moment?

32:40.996 --> 32:41.838
Because we're on mission.

32:42.661 --> 32:43.824
This is our mission mandate.

32:46.031 --> 32:46.994
We're equipping you.

33:07.586 --> 33:08.947
All right.

33:08.967 --> 33:09.488
Shh.

33:09.508 --> 33:09.828
Okay.

33:12.130 --> 33:13.952
You can recycle your little piece of plastic.

33:13.972 --> 33:15.194
You can put it in the bin on the way out.

33:16.335 --> 33:17.856
Be a good steward of God's planet.

33:23.121 --> 33:24.963
Our third and final mandate is this.

33:35.574 --> 33:35.954
All right.

33:37.698 --> 33:40.281
Our mission requires action.

33:41.743 --> 33:45.307
Jesus said in the Great Commission, therefore go.

33:46.588 --> 33:47.609
So that's what we're going to do.

33:49.231 --> 33:52.314
God never moves through good intention.

33:52.915 --> 33:55.078
He moves for obedience.

33:56.359 --> 33:57.380
Seeing is not enough.

33:58.722 --> 33:59.903
Agreeing is not enough.

34:01.365 --> 34:02.786
Praying is not even enough.

34:03.707 --> 34:06.130
Our mission requires action.

34:08.994 --> 34:10.175
So we've got to move this year.

34:13.118 --> 34:17.542
Chantal and I, we want to motivate you through the gospel to have someone sitting with you in church.

34:18.723 --> 34:22.507
This time next year, who does not know Christ, who's found him.

34:26.771 --> 34:32.456
When God asked the people of Israel, whom shall I send?

34:33.598 --> 34:38.322
Isaiah said this, he spoke up and he said, here I am,

34:39.554 --> 34:40.135
Send me.

34:41.557 --> 34:42.298
Here I am.

34:43.139 --> 34:43.560
Send me.

34:45.042 --> 34:46.163
Do you know your smile?

34:47.766 --> 34:48.727
You holding a door?

34:49.328 --> 34:50.449
You giving someone a hug?

34:51.190 --> 34:52.692
You serving in the supermarket?

34:53.293 --> 34:55.296
You putting your time in the container?

34:56.938 --> 35:02.406
You sharing the love of Jesus with someone at university could be the one thing that saves a life.

35:03.868 --> 35:05.170
I want to finish with this story.

35:07.490 --> 35:11.256
On anointing Sunday, an individual came down the front and I happened to pray for them.

35:11.977 --> 35:14.821
And they said, can I just share a story with you?

35:14.841 --> 35:20.530
They said, on Christmas Eve, I'd made a decision to take my life.

35:22.212 --> 35:25.217
I planned it, I bought everything I needed to.

35:33.429 --> 35:36.914
And they said that before they carried it, carried through,

35:38.402 --> 35:42.968
They wanted to come and make their peace with God at Christmas Eve service here.

35:45.913 --> 35:59.632
When they came into this atmosphere of love and care and the smiles and the hugs and the friendship in this place, God spoke to them and said, you can't carry this on.

35:59.652 --> 36:04.258
They made a decision to not go through with it.

36:04.278 --> 36:05.720
We're supporting and we're counseling.

36:05.780 --> 36:06.962
We're loving that individual.

36:08.322 --> 36:09.564
Why am I telling that story?

36:10.565 --> 36:15.070
Because you don't know when your own mission, that your mission is saving lives.

36:15.791 --> 36:21.238
I don't know who offered the hug or the bed, the love of Christ in an outward focused way.

36:22.099 --> 36:27.005
Church, so many lives depend on what we do.

36:27.025 --> 36:29.748
We can be a gathering church or we can be a going church.

36:31.110 --> 36:37.778
But this year, our focus is to be a going church, to go into all the world

36:38.050 --> 36:46.458
Those who are on the edge, those who are on the brink, those who are hurting, hungry, broken, destitute, those who feel like they cannot live one ever day.

36:47.819 --> 36:48.780
God, here I am.

36:49.821 --> 36:51.083
Send me.

36:51.103 --> 36:54.085
You say, I'm going to accept the mission today.

36:54.105 --> 36:56.027
I want you to stand to your feet.

36:56.047 --> 36:57.749
I want you to stand to your feet.

36:57.769 --> 37:01.553
And I want you to lift up our hand with a little band on.

37:02.133 --> 37:04.716
It's just a sign to say, God, I'm on mission this year.

37:05.977 --> 37:06.517
Here I am.

37:06.637 --> 37:07.218
Send me.

37:08.322 --> 37:10.666
Here I am, here I am.

37:11.828 --> 37:18.218
I know I've got a lot of, got a lot of my own issues, but I'm deciding this year.

37:18.599 --> 37:19.901
God, I don't need another snack.

37:21.003 --> 37:22.525
God, I'm focused on who's lost.

37:23.627 --> 37:27.834
I'm focused on the lost person at school, uni college, in my workplace.

37:27.894 --> 37:29.437
God, here I am, send me.

37:29.857 --> 37:31.380
God, use me this year.

37:32.021 --> 37:33.784
Use my smile, use my hug.

37:33.804 --> 37:35.186
I don't feel like I have a lot.

37:35.490 --> 37:38.675
I don't even know if I have the confidence to share my story.

37:38.696 --> 37:40.338
But God, I have something.

37:40.358 --> 37:41.160
So here I am.

37:41.721 --> 37:42.182
Use me.

37:42.282 --> 37:42.682
Send me.

37:42.742 --> 37:45.307
I want you to lift your hand and say, I'm on mission.

37:45.327 --> 37:46.188
I'm on mission 2026.

37:46.689 --> 37:47.591
I'm on mission.

37:48.552 --> 37:49.234
I'm on mission.

37:50.476 --> 37:51.117
I'm searching.

37:51.137 --> 37:56.005
I'm seeking for those who are lost in my world.

37:56.025 --> 37:56.907
Thank you, Jesus.

37:56.927 --> 37:58.770
Lord, you see every hand right now.

37:59.202 --> 38:05.328
We are an army, Father God, on mission to serve the greatest cause on earth, Jesus Christ.

38:05.989 --> 38:09.232
And Lord, we would lay our differences aside.

38:09.292 --> 38:11.074
We would lay down the small things.

38:11.414 --> 38:14.918
Lord, we don't need any more Christian snacks, Father God.

38:15.178 --> 38:16.840
Lord, you've already given us enough.

38:17.120 --> 38:19.022
And so we march forward this day.

38:19.242 --> 38:22.786
We move forward with Jesus beside us, Father.

38:22.806 --> 38:24.768
We're gonna take ground, Father God.

38:24.788 --> 38:26.610
We're gonna see countless souls.

38:26.690 --> 38:28.813
find Jesus in 2026.

38:29.013 --> 38:32.338
If you believe it, come on, let's sing this out together.

38:32.599 --> 38:33.640
In Jesus' name.

38:36.224 --> 38:39.028
Growing up, I was always taught that mission was a place.

38:40.390 --> 38:41.312
You go on mission.

38:42.193 --> 38:43.395
You know, mission isn't a place.

38:43.475 --> 38:45.718
Mission is a person.

38:45.738 --> 38:50.586
And actually, God this year was to send you to a person.

38:50.606 --> 38:51.587
Now, that's out of place.

38:52.208 --> 38:53.430
And it could be a broad.

38:53.450 --> 38:54.491
It could be in a different city.

38:55.613 --> 38:56.274
I'm not going to get it.

38:56.962 --> 39:00.726
play on words, but mission is always a person.

39:00.746 --> 39:05.350
God's mission this year is for you to seek and to save that which is lost.

39:07.732 --> 39:11.255
So I want you just to think about a person right now who's lost.

39:12.397 --> 39:14.478
Like that mother did with her child earlier to me.

39:14.519 --> 39:17.561
I want you to think about someone, maybe they're so far gone.

39:19.023 --> 39:26.770
Maybe they even, they hate the church or they're so anti God, you're thinking how on earth God, could you ever reach that person?

39:27.810 --> 39:32.737
God can reach the furthest heart, but He will use you as part of His process.

39:33.879 --> 39:38.445
You are His hands and His feet to this world.

39:38.465 --> 39:44.153
So if you have a person right now in mind, I want you to lift your hand right now.

39:44.173 --> 39:46.797
Nobody, nobody is too far gone.

39:48.219 --> 39:49.160
Nobody is too old.

39:55.009 --> 39:55.890
What, right now?

39:57.346 --> 40:00.791
Every hand represents a soul this year who's lost.

40:01.793 --> 40:04.758
And your heart is to seek and to save those who are lost.

40:05.479 --> 40:21.144
So we pray for sons and daughters, for dads and mums, for grandparents, for neighbors, for work colleagues, for those who sit in our lecture theatres, Father, who are so far away from you that you would right now begin to work on their hearts, Lord.

40:21.164 --> 40:25.010
As we go on mission with kindness and love and care,

40:25.922 --> 40:31.049
that you would Father give us doors this year to walk through, to share the gospel.

40:31.890 --> 40:37.317
Give us words, Father God, to melt the hardest hearts.

40:37.337 --> 40:42.684
We pray for a harvest of souls in 2026.

40:43.606 --> 40:48.392
The fields are white unto harvest.

40:49.373 --> 40:55.922
May there be many laborers in your vineyard here in Soul Church in Jesus' name.

40:57.090 --> 40:58.132
Amen.

40:58.152 --> 40:58.552
Amen.

40:59.674 --> 41:00.375
We're on mission.

41:03.720 --> 41:06.304
I want to just pray for one more group of people, and we're going to get out of here.

41:06.324 --> 41:08.388
I know we've got a little bit late, but it's a special Sunday.

41:08.408 --> 41:11.312
I want to ask you this one question.

41:12.734 --> 41:16.120
Please, if you can just stay still just for one moment, it's the most important time of the service.

41:16.881 --> 41:19.325
I want to give you an opportunity to receive Jesus.

41:20.086 --> 41:25.234
You say you've heard that today, and as you were speaking about that lost sheep, that lost coin, that

41:25.410 --> 41:28.875
that lost person or that you are that lost person.

41:29.375 --> 41:31.618
You feel lost, maybe a friend brought you here today.

41:31.659 --> 41:40.691
You feel away from God or you just never had relationship with God, but you feel like, man, I am lost and God, I need you to save me today.

41:40.791 --> 41:42.493
My life is tore up.

41:43.415 --> 41:45.197
Done so many things that I'm ashamed of.

41:45.257 --> 41:48.241
I'm hurting, I'm lonely, I'm broken.

41:48.261 --> 41:51.906
Whatever your situation is, God wants to meet you where you're at today.

41:53.528 --> 41:54.770
And the church's mission

41:54.882 --> 41:58.628
is to help you find Jesus, is to help you today.

41:59.669 --> 42:13.951
So if you say, John, I'm lost, but I wanna ask Jesus to help me find purpose in this life, hope for this life, and assurance that one day when I leave this life, I'll spend eternity in heaven with him.

42:14.432 --> 42:15.794
If that's you all over this room.

42:16.194 --> 42:16.735
online.

42:16.835 --> 42:18.076
Here's what I want you to do if you're in the room.

42:18.337 --> 42:20.579
I want you to just lift up your hand right now and say, I need Jesus.

42:21.040 --> 42:21.741
I need Jesus.

42:21.761 --> 42:22.302
I need Jesus.

42:22.522 --> 42:23.783
Just lift it up all around this room.

42:23.903 --> 42:24.464
I need Jesus.

42:24.765 --> 42:25.626
Lift it up nice and high.

42:25.666 --> 42:26.647
Wait a minute.

42:26.667 --> 42:27.568
I need Jesus today.

42:28.129 --> 42:28.669
God bless you.

42:29.330 --> 42:30.692
I need Jesus.

42:30.712 --> 42:32.154
I need Jesus.

42:32.174 --> 42:32.814
I need Jesus.

42:36.199 --> 42:37.080
Lift it up nice and high.

42:37.120 --> 42:38.962
Maybe just bring the house side to have a fraction.

42:48.578 --> 42:51.562
I need Jesus, just lift your hand up one second, I can't see everyone.

42:51.663 --> 42:53.746
Okay, if you lift it up your hand, I want you to come right now.

42:53.946 --> 42:56.049
You come, come down the front, I want to pray for you.

42:56.430 --> 43:01.277
You come, even if you didn't lift up your hand, if you say I need Jesus, I want you to come, come out of your seat.

43:01.818 --> 43:03.380
Come down, come down the front.

43:04.101 --> 43:04.502
That's it.

43:05.223 --> 43:06.425
You come.

43:06.445 --> 43:08.127
Bring a friend, if you want to bring a friend.

43:09.189 --> 43:13.816
If you lift it up your hand, you come.

43:13.836 --> 43:16.039
We'll wait for you, come on, we'll keep cheering, we're gonna wait.

43:16.740 --> 43:17.842
People come in to Jesus.

43:22.114 --> 43:33.411
You come right now and you set that prayer for your heart and you know that you need Jesus as your Lord and Savior.

43:33.431 --> 43:35.975
That's it.

43:35.995 --> 43:36.175
You come.

43:36.195 --> 43:36.415
Incredible.

43:36.435 --> 43:39.520
Amazing.

43:39.540 --> 43:43.165
It takes a lot of courage to step out of your seat.

43:43.185 --> 43:45.629
We'll wait for you.

43:45.649 --> 43:48.012
Amazing.

43:48.032 --> 43:48.253
That's it.

43:48.273 --> 43:49.074
You come.

44:38.498 --> 44:40.981
to say a prayer right now and it's a prayer from the heart.

44:41.861 --> 44:48.188
What it does is it transitions us from our old life, trying to get through life on our own, our sin, our baggage.

44:49.109 --> 44:51.952
We let go of that and we come into a new life of Jesus.

44:52.973 --> 44:59.259
He wants you to know today that all of your sin, your mistakes from your past, you're leaving here at the full of the cross.

45:00.100 --> 45:05.906
So when you accept Jesus, he forgives all of your past, all of your sin.

45:07.010 --> 45:09.232
And we've all set this prayer at some point in this room.

45:10.513 --> 45:12.635
And the Bible then causes a new creation.

45:12.795 --> 45:14.097
We're literally created again.

45:14.477 --> 45:16.319
It's where you heard the word born again, Christian.

45:16.339 --> 45:17.520
Sounds a bit weird, I get it.

45:18.861 --> 45:21.364
But what it is is we find new life.

45:22.204 --> 45:27.750
The old life lets us down, but new life, Jesus will never fail us and never let us down.

45:27.770 --> 45:29.611
So I want us to say this prayer to God out loud.

45:30.032 --> 45:33.135
Dear Lord Jesus, thank you for dying for me.

45:34.376 --> 45:36.498
To forgive all my sins and failures.

45:37.954 --> 45:42.879
I believe that you rose from the dead so that I could have a brand new life.

45:44.321 --> 45:53.470
Please come into my heart and help me by the power of the Holy Spirit, to trust and to live for you.

45:53.490 --> 45:55.192
Amen.

45:55.492 --> 45:56.413
Amen.

45:56.433 --> 45:59.296
Can we congratulate everyone who set that prayer?

46:02.960 --> 46:03.581
This is Ben.

46:03.801 --> 46:04.882
Ben, just give us a wave.

46:05.314 --> 46:08.039
Ben and his wife Patricia, they're going to be in, there's a little chapel.

46:08.059 --> 46:10.002
We're going to give you a Bible and some information.

46:10.263 --> 46:13.007
He's going to slip into there and then come straight back into the service.

46:13.268 --> 46:15.231
So why don't you just head to my left, you're right.

46:15.251 --> 46:18.597
Let's give these guys a big hand as they receive their Bibles.

46:20.540 --> 46:23.004
I'm going to come down and shake your hands as well.

46:27.612 --> 46:30.898
We're on mission, 2026.

46:36.450 --> 46:38.092
We're not snacking.

46:38.112 --> 46:38.673
We're going.

46:39.794 --> 46:46.804
We're going into our workplaces, into our universities, our colleges, and we're going to share the greatest love story ever.

46:46.824 --> 46:50.469
That Jesus is the hope of the world.

46:51.090 --> 46:52.291
Amen.

46:52.992 --> 46:56.056
Amen.

46:56.197 --> 46:57.298
God bless you.

46:57.474 --> 47:05.302
If you said yes to Jesus today by saying the Salvation Prayer, we'd love for you to email connections at soulchurch.com.

47:05.602 --> 47:10.166
So we can talk to you a little bit more about this incredible decision you've just made.

47:10.807 --> 47:18.474
And if at any point in the service, you felt moved to give towards any of our local or global initiatives, head to soulchurch.com.

47:19.275 --> 47:26.322
And don't forget to stay connected with us on Facebook, Instagram, and YouTube by searching at Soul Church UK.

47:26.594 --> 47:28.146
Take care and God bless.

